Preheat the oven to 240C/220C Fan/Gas 9.Boil the chips in lightly salted water for 4 minutes, then drain well in a colander. When cool enough to handle, tip them onto a baking tray and drizzle over the oil. Mix to coat the chips in the oil, then arrange them in a single layer and season with salt and pepper.Bake for 20 minutes. Turn the chips, season again, then bake for 15 minutes more.